ss=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 03, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lla1665702682181.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lla1665702682181.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lla1665702682181.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lla1665702682181\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"lla1665702682181__unoasync_406561\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Disable the handling of asynchronous messages by the application.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"lla1665702682181__topic_d122546e1_d122547e1_d122548e1\">\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"lla1665702682181__p_d122549e1_d122550e1_d122551e1\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" id=\"lla1665702682181__codeblock_cjc_2f2_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">int unoasync();</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lla1665702682181__topic_d86752e1_d86753e1_d86754e1_d86755e1_d86756e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d493440e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lla1665702682181__d6420e20\">None</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lla1665702682181__topic_d86757e1_d86758e1_d86759e1_d86760e1_d86761e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d493440e70\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"lla1665702682181__table_d14936e1_d14937e1_d14938e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by unoasync</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lla1665702682181__table_d14936e1_d14937e1_d14938e1__entry__1\">Value </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lla1665702682181__table_d14936e1_d14937e1_d14938e1__entry__2\">Meaning </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lla1665702682181__table_d14936e1_d14937e1_d14938e1__entry__1\">\n 0\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lla1665702682181__table_d14936e1_d14937e1_d14938e1__entry__2\">Successful completion </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lla1665702682181__table_d14936e1_d14937e1_d14938e1__entry__1\">-4 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lla1665702682181__table_d14936e1_d14937e1_d14938e1__entry__2\">The IPC message queue could not be closed\n                        and/or removed </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lla1665702682181__table_d14936e1_d14937e1_d14938e1__entry__1\">-5 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lla1665702682181__table_d14936e1_d14937e1_d14938e1__entry__2\">Asynchronous messages were not enabled </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lla1665702682181__topic_d86762e1_d86763e1_d86764e1_d86765e1_d86766e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d493440e131\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lla1665702682181__d6610e20\">Unix platforms only (except Tru64 Unix). Library:\n          <span class=\"ph filepath\">yrtl</span>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lla1665702682181__topic_d86767e1_d86768e1_d86769e1_d86770e1_d86771e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d493440e144\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lla1665702682181__p_d122570e1_d122571e1_d122572e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">unoasync</code> disables the handling of\n            asynchronous messages by the calling application. It closes and removes the IPC message\n            queue, and terminates the handler thread. It is not required to call this function when\n            exiting the application, because that will automatically close and remove the queue and\n            terminate the handler thread.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lla1665702682181__p_d122573e1_d122574e1_d122575e1\">Typically you would not call\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">unoasync</code> directly from ProcScript (although it is possible to do so\n            by using a C signature), but from a routine in your user 3GL code that also contains the\n            call to <code class=\"ph codeph\">uasync</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"lla1665702682181__note_evs_mf2_bwb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Although the <code class=\"ph codeph\">unoasync</code> function\n            still works, it is recommended that you not use it. The handling of asynchronous\n            messages has been replaced by an integrated solution, which can be enabled by including\n            the assignment setting of <code class=\"ph codeph\">$IPC_ASYNC</code>.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lla1665702682181__section_fvs_mf2_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d493440e173\">Example: uasync and unoasync</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following 3GL code defines a handler that passes the message to the\n            application’s receiveMessage trigger, as well as logging an informational message in the\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">syslog</span> file (this particular action is specific to Unix). The\n            application would perform or activate ASYNC_INIT at the start of the application’s\n            receiveMessage trigger.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104lla1665702682181_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"lla1665702682181__codeblock_vvd_4f2_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n#include &lt;syslog.h&gt;\n\nint HANDLER (unsigned char* msg, short len)\n{\nchar buf[500];\nstrncpy(buf, msg, len); /* Copy the message */\nbuf[len] = 0; /* Add the zero terminator */\nuputames((unsigned char *)buf, len);/* Pass message to ASYNC trigger */\nsyslog(LOG_INFO, buf); /* Write message to system log file */\nreturn 1; /* Return any value (it is not used) */\n}\n\nint ASYNC_INIT ()\n{ return uasync(HANDLER); }\nint ASYNC_DEINIT ()\n{ return unoasync(); }</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/snx1665702681980.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uasync</a><p>Initialize the Uniface application to receive asynchronous messages.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vli1665702682321.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$IPC_ASYNC</a><p>Create a thread that listens for interprocess communication (IPC) messages.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529617\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529617\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "unoasync Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 03, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Disable the handling of asynchronous messages by the application. int unoasync(); Copy Parameters None Return Values Table 1. Values returned by unoasync Value Meaning 0 Successful completion -4 The IPC message queue could not be closed and/or removed -5 Asynchronous messages were not enabled Use Unix platforms only (except Tru64 Unix). Library: yrtl . Description unoasync disables the handling of asynchronous messages by the calling application. It closes and removes the IPC message queue, and terminates the handler thread. It is not required to call this function when exiting the application, because that will automatically close and remove the queue and terminate the handler thread. Typically you would not call unoasync directly from ProcScript (although it is possible to do so by using a C signature), but from a routine in your user 3GL code that also contains the call to uasync . Note: Although the unoasync function still works, it is recommended that you not use it. The handling of asynchronous messages has been replaced by an integrated solution, which can be enabled by including the assignment setting of $IPC_ASYNC . Example: uasync and unoasync The following 3GL code defines a handler that passes the message to the application’s receiveMessage trigger, as well as logging an informational message in the syslog file (this particular action is specific to Unix). The application would perform or activate ASYNC_INIT at the start of the application’s receiveMessage trigger. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> #include <syslog.h> int HANDLER (unsigned char* msg, short len) { char buf[500]; strncpy(buf, msg, len); /* Copy the message */ buf[len] = 0; /* Add the zero terminator */ uputames((unsigned char *)buf, len);/* Pass message to ASYNC trigger */ syslog(LOG_INFO, buf); /* Write message to system log file */ return 1; /* Return any value (it is not used) */ } int ASYNC_INIT () { return uasync(HANDLER); } int ASYNC_DEINIT () { return unoasync(); } Copy Related Links uasync Initialize the Uniface application to receive asynchronous messages. $IPC_ASYNC Create a thread that listens for interprocess communication (IPC) messages. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}